	('ca7ce6b4-8e9c-49ab-8a7e-2a5c980a13e3', 'image_analysis', 'image_analysis', '{"type": "object", "required": ["image"], "properties": {"image": {"type": "string"}, "context": {"type": "string"}, "focus_areas": {"type": "array", "items": {"type": "string"}}, "analysis_type": {"enum": ["general", "artistic", "technical", "child_drawing"], "type": "string"}, "user_instructions": {"type": "string"}}}', '{"type": "object", "required": ["response"], "properties": {"response": {"type": "string", "minLength": 10}, "artistic_notes": {"type": "string"}, "technical_notes": {"type": "string"}, "confidence_score": {"type": "number", "maximum": 1, "minimum": 0}, "identified_elements": {"type": "array", "items": {"type": "string"}}}}', 'You are an assistant that helps a child explain their drawing so it can be recreated as a professional-quality line drawing. Always follow these steps in order: Shape Inventory List all visible parts of the drawing as simple shapes (ovals, blobs, lines, circles). Include head, limbs, eyes, mouth, base, connectors, and decorations. Interpretation Options For each part, suggest 2–3 possible interpretations. Keep them playful, age-appropriate, and neutral. Organize by function (face feature, body part, accessory, decoration). Ambiguity Scan Assign confidence (High / Medium / Low). Mark all Low confidence parts for clarification.', '{"type": "object", "required": ["response"], "properties": {"response": {"type": "string", "minLength": 10}, "artistic_notes": {"type": "string"}, "technical_notes": {"type": "string"}, "confidence_score": {"type": "number", "maximum": 1, "minimum": 0}, "identified_elements": {"type": "array", "items": {"type": "string"}}}}', 'gpt-4o', 'json_object', 4000, 0.7, true, '2025-09-05 19:00:12.701482+00', '2025-09-06 01:55:54.625321+00', 10),
	('2aa869e5-ff94-4329-bb42-e85cb30fdfcf', 'image_generation', 'image_generation', '{"type": "object", "required": ["prompt"], "properties": {"prompt": {"type": "string", "minLength": 10}}}', '{"type": "object", "required": ["image_base64"], "properties": {"response": {"type": "string"}, "image_base64": {"type": "string"}}}', 'Final Line Drawing Spec Produce one complete, unambiguous description for an illustrator. Include: Head/face features (eyes, mouth, nose, teeth, horns, etc.) Limbs/appendages (arms, legs, wings, stalks, etc.) Base/connector/outline shape Accessories/decorations (patterns, clothing-like details) Notes on relative size, symmetry, and style consistency create a prompt for a polished line drawing description that stays true to the child’s intent which incorporates all of the answers and clarifications and analysis gathered. 

From that prompt, generate an image which stays tru to the child''s drawing but incorporates all of the ideas into one coherent professional illustration.  Keep it fun, kid friendly and playful.', '{"type": "object", "required": ["image_base64"], "properties": {"image_base64": {"type": "string"}}}', 'dall-e-3', 'json_object', NULL, NULL, true, '2025-09-05 19:00:12.701482+00', '2025-09-06 02:08:45.883087+00', 40),
	('8ec4530c-5f64-464d-9b85-b4a9992e90d6', 'questions_generation', 'questions_generation', '{"type": "object", "required": ["analysis"], "properties": {"analysis": {"type": "string"}}}', '{"type": "object", "required": ["questions"], "properties": {"response": {"type": "string"}, "questions": {"type": "array", "items": {"type": "object", "required": ["id", "text", "type", "options", "required"], "properties": {"id": {"type": "string"}, "text": {"type": "string", "minLength": 10}, "type": {"enum": ["multiple_choice"], "type": "string"}, "options": {"type": "array", "items": {"type": "string"}, "maxItems": 6, "minItems": 2}, "required": {"type": "boolean"}}}, "maxItems": 15, "minItems": 3}}}', 'Based on the image analysis, generate 3-5 kid-friendly questions to clarify ambiguous parts of the drawing. Each question should be short (no more than 12 words) and provide 2-3 clear answer choices. Focus on identifying unclear elements like body parts, objects, or features that need clarification.

Return your response as a JSON object with a "questions" array. Each question should have: id, text, type (always "multiple_choice"), options (array of 2-3 choices), and required (boolean).

Example format:
{
  "questions": [
    {
      "id": "q1",
      "text": "What is this part?",
      "type": "multiple_choice",
      "options": ["eyes", "teeth", "decoration"],
      "required": true
    }
  ]
